Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia's President Boris Yeltsin has signed a decree 
confirming the composition of the Council for Cadre Policy under 
the Russian head of state. It will consist of 17 people, 
including First Vice Premier Oleg Soskovets; Presidential 
Administration Chief Sergey Filatov; Federation Council Chairman 
Vladimir Shumeyko; Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev; and Moscow 
Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov. 
  By another decree, the president appointed Boris Tyulkov his 
representative in Omsk Oblast. 

